  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening NGO Roles and Capabilities to Scale-up Agricultural Development</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of this project is to support country-owned agricultural development and reduce rural poverty in developing countries by identifying NGO best practice pathways for local partner capacity building and to provide food security experts with comprehensive, relevant data in an accessible, user-friendly way to promote more informed decisions about policy and programming. The three objectives are to 1) identify success factors and constraints to effective NGO capacity building in food security and agriculture through a review of the Best Practices and Innovations Initiative and consultations with key stakeholders; 2) strengthen capabilities of selected local civil society partners; and 3) expand InterAction&#xC6;s Food Security Aid Map with additional data and functionality based on consultations with food security experts and IFAD.</narrative>
  </description>
